{
  "text": "We are now ready to see how the wall-crossing phenomena can be understood in the presence of the non-vanishing electric field F 08 on the D3-brane. We count the number of BPS strings on the D5-D3 system, as in section 3. The only difference from section 3 is the \"slope\" of the strings induced by the electric field F 08 = 0. Let us first consider the limiting case of Im z = +\u221e. Recall that Im z represents the relative position of the D5-brane in x 9 -direction. So, the limit Im z = +\u221e corresponds to moving the D5-brane far right in Fig. 4 . Then, all the BPS D5-D3 and D3-D5 strings considered in the previous section still exist, and the corresponding BPS partition function is the same as [CITATION_1] , that is,",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "14194090"
